Expression : A single line of instruction containing operands and opearator
Operand: A variable or value which is in a expression
Conditional Statement: Statement which are executed based on condition
Statement Block: The code block which get executed when certain condition is satisfied
Infinite Loop: The loop which never ends

2. When does a while statement stop looping ?
Ans. When the conditional expr is false

3. When does a until statement stop looping ?
Ans. When the conditional expr is True

